concord, n.h. _ new hampshire primary voters put their often unpredictable mark on the 1988 presidential campaign today, with massachusetts gov. michael dukakis hoping for a neighborly boost from the inmocrats. on the republican side, bob dole hoped to make it two victories a row while george bush banked on a comeback
