the foreign tour will begin in august in athens, greece, with possible performances later in italy, southern france and spain
rostropovich, who fled the soviet union in 1974 because of artistic restrictions, was non-committal when asked whether he hoped to take the national symphony on a tour of his homeland. if soviet authorities extend an invitation, he told reporters, ``then we will respond.''
